File: Health Minister Zweli Mkhize. JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize is warning South Africans that the battle against COVID-19 is not over yet. South Africa moves to lockdown Alert Level 1 on Monday, with the easing of many more restrictions. Mkhize says SA is not out of the woods and is urging people to comply with regulations. READ: Mkhize: SA passing the COVID-19 peak "We are now searching for the vaccine, but before we get the vaccine, we can't rest. South Africans need to know that level 1 isn't like everything is over," he said. Mkhize also says there is still a risk of a second wave of COVID-19 infections. "We have to make sure we take precautions. This COVID-19 can still resurge. We must not lose the message and be complacent." South Africans will have more freedom under Level 1 from Monday. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.